---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Hedge Bet Calculator"
  description="Use this free hedge bet calculator to calculate back and lay hedge stakes, lay liability, commission and profit or loss across both outcomes."
>
  <section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Betting calculator</p>
    <h1>Hedge Bet Calculator</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Use this calculator to work out a hedge stake when backing and laying, including exchange commission and lay liability.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Quick explanation:</strong> Hedging often involves backing first and laying later, or laying first and backing later. This calculator shows the hedge stake and the result if the selection wins or loses.
    </div>

    <div class="calculator-panel" id="hedge-calculator">
      <div class="calculator-header">
        <div>
          <h2>Choose your hedge type</h2>
          <p>Select whether you backed first or laid first, then enter the odds and commission.</p>
        </div>
        <button class="button secondary small-button" type="button" id="reset-hedge">
          Reset example
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="mode-tabs" role="group" aria-label="Hedge type">
        <button class="mode-tab active" type="button" data-mode="back-first">
          Back first, then lay
        </button>
        <button class="mode-tab" type="button" data-mode="lay-first">
          Lay first, then back
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="input-grid">
        <label class="input-group">
          <span id="original-stake-label">Back stake</span>
          <div class="money-input-wrap">
            <span>£</span>
            <input id="original-stake" type="number" min="0.01" step="0.01" value="100" />
          </div>
          <small id="original-stake-help">The amount you originally backed.</small>
        </label>

        <label class="input-group">
          <span id="original-odds-label">Back odds</span>
          <input id="original-odds" type="number" min="1.01" step="0.01" value="3.00" />
          <small id="original-odds-help">The decimal odds of your original back bet.</small>
        </label>

        <label class="input-group">
          <span id="hedge-odds-label">Lay odds</span>
          <input id="hedge-odds" type="number" min="1.01" step="0.01" value="2.00" />
          <small id="hedge-odds-help">The decimal odds available for the hedge lay bet.</small>
        </label>

        <label class="input-group">
          <span>Exchange commission</span>
          <div class="percent-input-wrap">
            <input id="commission" type="number" min="0" max="99" step="0.1" value="2" />
            <span>%</span>
          </div>
          <small>Commission charged on exchange winnings.</small>
        </label>
      </div>

      <div class="results-grid">
        <div class="result-card">
          <span id="hedge-stake-label">Lay stake</span>
          <strong id="hedge-stake-result">£151.52</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="result-card">
          <span>Lay liability</span>
          <strong id="lay-liability-result">£151.52</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="result-card">
          <span>If selection wins</span>
          <strong id="selection-wins-result">£48.48</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="result-card">
          <span>If selection loses</span>
          <strong id="selection-loses-result">£48.48</strong>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="result-note" id="result-note">
        A lay stake of £151.52 would balance the result at £48.48 profit whether the selection wins or loses.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>What is hedging a bet?</h2>
    <p>
      Hedging a bet means placing another bet to reduce risk, lock in a result, or balance the profit and loss across different outcomes.
    </p>
    <p>
      In exchange betting, hedging often involves a combination of backing and laying. You might back a selection first and then lay it later, or lay a selection first and then back it later.
    </p>

    <h2>What does backing mean?</h2>
    <p>
      A back bet is the traditional type of bet. You are betting that something will happen. If the selection wins, you make a profit based on the odds. If the selection loses, you lose your stake.
    </p>

    <h2>What does laying mean?</h2>
    <p>
      A lay bet is the opposite side of a back bet. When you lay a selection, you are betting that it will not win. If the selection loses, you win the other person’s stake, minus any exchange commission. If the selection wins, you pay out the liability.
    </p>

    <h2>What is lay liability?</h2>
    <p>
      Lay liability is the amount you risk when placing a lay bet. It is calculated from the lay stake and the lay odds.
    </p>

    <div class="formula-box">
      <p><strong>Lay liability</strong> = lay stake × (lay odds − 1)</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Back first, then lay</h2>
    <p>
      This is common when you back a selection at higher odds and later lay it at lower odds. This can be used to balance profit across both outcomes, sometimes called greening up.
    </p>

    <div class="formula-box">
      <p><strong>Lay stake</strong> = back stake × back odds ÷ (lay odds − commission)</p>
      <p><strong>If selection wins</strong> = back profit − lay liability</p>
      <p><strong>If selection loses</strong> = lay stake after commission − back stake</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Lay first, then back</h2>
    <p>
      Sometimes a trader may lay a selection first, hoping the odds drift, then back it later at higher odds. The hedge bet is then a back bet rather than a lay bet.
    </p>

    <div class="formula-box">
      <p><strong>Back stake</strong> = lay stake × (lay odds − commission) ÷ back odds</p>
      <p><strong>If selection wins</strong> = back profit − lay liability</p>
      <p><strong>If selection loses</strong> = lay stake after commission − back stake</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Example: back first, then lay</h2>
    <p>
      Suppose you back a selection with £100 at odds of 3.00. Later, you can lay the same selection at odds of 2.00 with 2% exchange commission.
    </p>

    <table class="example-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Input</th>
          <th>Value</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Back stake</td>
          <td>£100.00</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Back odds</td>
          <td>3.00</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Lay odds</td>
          <td>2.00</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Commission</td>
          <td>2%</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Lay stake</td>
          <td>£151.52</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>
      In this example, the calculator balances the position so the profit is approximately the same whether the selection wins or loses.
    </p>

    <h2>Can hedging guarantee profit?</h2>
    <p>
      Hedging can sometimes lock in profit when odds have moved favourably, but it does not guarantee profit in every situation. If the prices are not favourable enough, hedging may simply reduce a loss or reduce the maximum possible profit.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Responsible note:</strong> Hedging, backing and laying are calculation methods. They can help you understand risk and exposure, but they do not remove betting risk.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Hedge bet calculator FAQs</h2>

    <h3>What does this hedge calculator do?</h3>
    <p>
      It calculates the hedge stake needed to balance the result across two outcomes when using back and lay bets.
    </p>

    <h3>Does the calculator include exchange commission?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. You can enter the exchange commission percentage. The calculator applies commission to the winning exchange side.
    </p>

    <h3>What is greening up?</h3>
    <p>
      Greening up is a common exchange betting phrase for spreading profit across all outcomes, so that the position shows a similar positive result whichever outcome occurs.
    </p>

    <h3>Why is my result showing a loss?</h3>
    <p>
      If the odds have not moved favourably enough, the hedge may balance the position at a loss. That can still reduce risk, but it does not create profit.
    </p>

    <h3>Is this a Betfair calculator?</h3>
    <p>
      This is a general back and lay hedge calculator. It can be used for exchange-style calculations, but a more specific Betfair calculator could later include more detailed settings and examples.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .calculator-panel {
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      padding: 1.25rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      background: #ffffff;
    }

    .calculator-header {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .calculator-header h2 {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .calculator-header p {
      margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .small-button {
      padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .mode-tabs {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding: 0.4rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
      width: fit-content;
    }

    .mode-tab {
      border: 0;
      border-radius: 999px;
      padding: 0.65rem 0.95rem;
      background: transparent;
      color: var(--color-muted);
      font: inherit;
      font-weight: 800;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .mode-tab.active {
      background: var(--color-green);
      color: white;
    }

    .input-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .input-group {
      display: block;
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
    }

    .input-group > span {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
      color: var(--color-navy);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .input-group input {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 0.75rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      color: var(--color-text);
      font: inherit;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      background: white;
    }

    .input-group input:focus {
      outline: 2px solid rgba(31, 138, 91, 0.22);
      border-color: var(--color-green);
    }

    .input-group small {
      display: block;
      margin-top: 0.45rem;
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .money-input-wrap,
    .percent-input-wrap {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      background: white;
    }

    .money-input-wrap span,
    .percent-input-wrap span {
      color: var(--color-muted);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .money-input-wrap input,
    .percent-input-wrap input {
      border: 0;
      padding: 0.5rem 0;
      background: transparent;
    }

    .money-input-wrap input:focus,
    .percent-input-wrap input:focus {
      outline: 0;
    }

    .results-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .result-card {
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
    }

    .result-card span {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
      color: var(--color-muted);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .result-card strong {
      display: block;
      color: var(--color-navy);
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      line-height: 1.2;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    .result-card strong.positive {
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
    }

    .result-card strong.negative {
      color: #b42318;
    }

    .result-note {
      margin: 1rem 0 0;
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: #eef8f3;
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .result-note.warning {
      background: #fff7e6;
      color: #8a5a00;
    }

    .result-note.error {
      background: #fff1f0;
      color: #b42318;
    }

    .article-section {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .formula-box {
      padding: 1rem 1.15rem;
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    .formula-box p {
      margin: 0.4rem 0;
    }

    .example-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .example-table th,
    .example-table td {
      padding: 0.75rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      text-align: left;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }

    .example-table th {
      color: var(--color-navy);
      background: #f4f7fa;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .example-table tr:last-child td {
      border-bottom: 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1120px) {
      .input-grid,
      .results-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 760px) {
      .calculator-header {
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .mode-tabs {
        width: 100%;
        border-radius: 16px;
      }

      .mode-tab {
        flex: 1 1 100%;
      }

      .input-grid,
      .results-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    const modeButtons = document.querySelectorAll(".mode-tab");
    const originalStakeInput = document.getElementById("original-stake");
    const originalOddsInput = document.getElementById("original-odds");
    const hedgeOddsInput = document.getElementById("hedge-odds");
    const commissionInput = document.getElementById("commission");
    const resetButton = document.getElementById("reset-hedge");

    const originalStakeLabel = document.getElementById("original-stake-label");
    const originalStakeHelp = document.getElementById("original-stake-help");
    const originalOddsLabel = document.getElementById("original-odds-label");
    const originalOddsHelp = document.getElementById("original-odds-help");
    const hedgeOddsLabel = document.getElementById("hedge-odds-label");
    const hedgeOddsHelp = document.getElementById("hedge-odds-help");

    const hedgeStakeLabel = document.getElementById("hedge-stake-label");
    const hedgeStakeResult = document.getElementById("hedge-stake-result");
    const layLiabilityResult = document.getElementById("lay-liability-result");
    const selectionWinsResult = document.getElementById("selection-wins-result");
    const selectionLosesResult = document.getElementById("selection-loses-result");
    const resultNote = document.getElementById("result-note");

    let currentMode = "back-first";

    function formatMoney(value) {
      return new Intl.NumberFormat("en-GB", {
        style: "currency",
        currency: "GBP",
        minimumFractionDigits: 2,
        maximumFractionDigits: 2
      }).format(value);
    }

    function setResultClass(element, value) {
      element.className = value >= 0 ? "positive" : "negative";
    }

    function showError(message) {
      hedgeStakeResult.textContent = "—";
      layLiabilityResult.textContent = "—";
      selectionWinsResult.textContent = "—";
      selectionLosesResult.textContent = "—";
      selectionWinsResult.className = "";
      selectionLosesResult.className = "";
      resultNote.textContent = message;
      resultNote.className = "result-note error";
    }

    function updateLabels() {
      if (currentMode === "back-first") {
        originalStakeLabel.textContent = "Back stake";
        originalStakeHelp.textContent = "The amount you originally backed.";
        originalOddsLabel.textContent = "Back odds";
        originalOddsHelp.textContent = "The decimal odds of your original back bet.";
        hedgeOddsLabel.textContent = "Lay odds";
        hedgeOddsHelp.textContent = "The decimal odds available for the hedge lay bet.";
        hedgeStakeLabel.textContent = "Lay stake";
      } else {
        originalStakeLabel.textContent = "Lay stake";
        originalStakeHelp.textContent = "The amount you originally laid.";
        originalOddsLabel.textContent = "Lay odds";
        originalOddsHelp.textContent = "The decimal odds of your original lay bet.";
        hedgeOddsLabel.textContent = "Back odds";
        hedgeOddsHelp.textContent = "The decimal odds available for the hedge back bet.";
        hedgeStakeLabel.textContent = "Back stake";
      }
    }

    function calculateHedge() {
      const originalStake = Number(originalStakeInput.value);
      const originalOdds = Number(originalOddsInput.value);
      const hedgeOdds = Number(hedgeOddsInput.value);
      const commissionPercent = Number(commissionInput.value);
      const commission = commissionPercent / 100;

      if (!Number.isFinite(originalStake) || originalStake <= 0) {
        showError("Please enter a stake greater than £0.");
        return;
      }

      if (!Number.isFinite(originalOdds) || originalOdds <= 1) {
        showError("Please enter decimal odds greater than 1.00 for the original bet.");
        return;
      }

      if (!Number.isFinite(hedgeOdds) || hedgeOdds <= 1) {
        showError("Please enter decimal odds greater than 1.00 for the hedge bet.");
        return;
      }

      if (!Number.isFinite(commissionPercent) || commissionPercent < 0 || commissionPercent >= 100) {
        showError("Please enter a commission percentage between 0 and 99.");
        return;
      }

      let hedgeStake;
      let layLiability;
      let selectionWinsProfit;
      let selectionLosesProfit;
      let noteStakeLabel;

      if (currentMode === "back-first") {
        const backStake = originalStake;
        const backOdds = originalOdds;
        const layOdds = hedgeOdds;

        hedgeStake = (backStake * backOdds) / (layOdds - commission);
        layLiability = hedgeStake * (layOdds - 1);

        selectionWinsProfit = (backStake * (backOdds - 1)) - layLiability;
        selectionLosesProfit = (hedgeStake * (1 - commission)) - backStake;
        noteStakeLabel = "lay stake";
      } else {
        const layStake = originalStake;
        const layOdds = originalOdds;
        const backOdds = hedgeOdds;

        hedgeStake = (layStake * (layOdds - commission)) / backOdds;
        layLiability = layStake * (layOdds - 1);

        selectionWinsProfit = (hedgeStake * (backOdds - 1)) - layLiability;
        selectionLosesProfit = (layStake * (1 - commission)) - hedgeStake;
        noteStakeLabel = "back stake";
      }

      if (!Number.isFinite(hedgeStake) || hedgeStake <= 0) {
        showError("These inputs do not produce a valid hedge stake.");
        return;
      }

      hedgeStakeResult.textContent = formatMoney(hedgeStake);
      layLiabilityResult.textContent = formatMoney(layLiability);
      selectionWinsResult.textContent = formatMoney(selectionWinsProfit);
      selectionLosesResult.textContent = formatMoney(selectionLosesProfit);

      setResultClass(selectionWinsResult, selectionWinsProfit);
      setResultClass(selectionLosesResult, selectionLosesProfit);

      const roundedDifference = Math.abs(selectionWinsProfit - selectionLosesProfit);

      if (selectionWinsProfit > 0.005 && selectionLosesProfit > 0.005) {
        resultNote.textContent = `A ${noteStakeLabel} of ${formatMoney(hedgeStake)} would balance the result at about ${formatMoney(selectionWinsProfit)} profit whether the selection wins or loses.`;
        resultNote.className = "result-note";
      } else if (selectionWinsProfit < -0.005 && selectionLosesProfit < -0.005) {
        resultNote.textContent = `This hedge balances the position, but both outcomes show a loss of about ${formatMoney(Math.abs(selectionWinsProfit))}.`;
        resultNote.className = "result-note warning";
      } else if (roundedDifference <= 0.02) {
        resultNote.textContent = `This hedge balances the two outcomes at approximately break-even.`;
        resultNote.className = "result-note";
      } else {
        resultNote.textContent = `This hedge reduces exposure, but the two outcomes are not perfectly equal after rounding.`;
        resultNote.className = "result-note warning";
      }
    }

    modeButtons.forEach((button) => {
      button.addEventListener("click", () => {
        currentMode = button.dataset.mode;

        modeButtons.forEach((modeButton) => {
          modeButton.classList.toggle("active", modeButton === button);
        });

        if (currentMode === "back-first") {
          originalStakeInput.value = "100";
          originalOddsInput.value = "3.00";
          hedgeOddsInput.value = "2.00";
          commissionInput.value = "2";
        } else {
          originalStakeInput.value = "100";
          originalOddsInput.value = "2.00";
          hedgeOddsInput.value = "3.00";
          commissionInput.value = "2";
        }

        updateLabels();
        calculateHedge();
      });
    });

    [originalStakeInput, originalOddsInput, hedgeOddsInput, commissionInput].forEach((input) => {
      input.addEventListener("input", calculateHedge);
    });

    resetButton.addEventListener("click", () => {
      currentMode = "back-first";

      modeButtons.forEach((button) => {
        button.classList.toggle("active", button.dataset.mode === "back-first");
      });

      originalStakeInput.value = "100";
      originalOddsInput.value = "3.00";
      hedgeOddsInput.value = "2.00";
      commissionInput.value = "2";

      updateLabels();
      calculateHedge();
    });

    updateLabels();
    calculateHedge();
  </script>
</MainLayout>
